  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare conventional breast imaging and diagnostic work-up (2
      dimensional imaging) to digital breast tomosynthesis (3 dimensional imaging) in the
      appearance of non-calcified breast masses. It is thought that non-calcified breast masses
      will be better visualized with the new 3D technology.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
